        "Learning a new language since children start to get to school has more benefits than drawbacks. There are several factors affecting the success of such a plan.",
        "The disadvantages of studying foreign languages in primary school years are significant. First and foremost, it will cause confusion for pupils since they have to recognize the difference in the way of using the new languages and their mother language. As well as they will get more pressure from learning too many subjects since they are too young. For example, in some families, their parents might send them to an English extra class after school with hope that they will get good marks in school. As a result, these pupil do not have enough time to play. These problems are enough to prove that learning more than one language may affect the growing up of children.",
